oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Crane on the Cumberland River, Nashville, Tennessee, 1956
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A view of a hoisting crane along the Cumberland River, in downtown Nashville, Tennessee, circa 1956. These photos relate to railroad freight cars of the Tennessee Central Railroad Company, located near the warehouse storage facility. Another method of freight and merchandise transportation was via the Cumberland River on barges. Forms part of Nashville Banner Negatives Collection. 1 photographic negative : b & w ; 4 x 5 in.
